# ── Secrets & billable keys — NEVER commit these ──────────────────────────
# Firebase Admin / service-account credentials (server-side, highly sensitive)
*serviceAccount*.json
*service-account*.json
firebase-adminsdk*.json
google-credentials*.json

# Environment / secret files
.env
.env.*
*.secret
secrets.*

# Anything holding a real Google Maps / Cloud API key.
# (In this project the Maps key is entered at runtime and lives only in the
#  browser's localStorage — it is NOT stored in any file. This block is a
#  guardrail in case a key file is ever added.)
maps-key*
*.apikey

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# NOTE: firebase-config.js is intentionally NOT ignored — the Firebase *web*
# config it contains is a public project identifier, safe to commit. Security
# comes from Firestore/Storage rules + App Check + plan limits, not secrecy.
